LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - EUROPE (02): RUSSIA (BASHKORTOSTAN) CATTLE, OIE
********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 29 Nov 2021
Source: OIE WAHIS [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=43411


Lumpy skin disease [LSD] virus (inf. with), Russia
----------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 25 Oct 2021
Confirmed: 24 Nov 2021
Reported: 29 Nov 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 28 Dec 2020
Causal agent: lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Turkmenevo 1, Baymakskiy rayon, Bashkortostan
Started: 25 Oct 2021
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 80 / 45 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures at event level
Control measures applied, domestic: control of vectors, disinfection, movement control inside the country, quarantine, screening, surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Bashkirskaya Veterinary Laboratory (local laboratory)
Species / Test / Outbreaks / Test date / Result
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 1 / 24 Nov 2021 / positive

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since August 2021, 32 outbreaks of lumpy skin disease (LSD) have been reported in Zabaykalye territory. The latest OIE follow-up report No 6 on 29 Nov 2021 is available at https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=43399.

"LSDV is not transmissible to humans. However, all laboratory manipulations must be performed at an appropriate containment level determined using biorisk analysis." https://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/eng/Health_standards/tahm/3.04.12_LSD.pdf

HealthMap/ProMED map of Bashkortostan Republic (Bashkiria), Russia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8699958,392]
